Patch 0079 — addresses user feedback: "still don't see THE CPU
bottleneck. Bottleneck not so old. why missing? update logic. don't do
static. do in logical way so all such are identified."

ROOT CAUSE
The HBM/CoWoS/CPU bottleneck signal exists in the system (via
SemiAnalysis articles) but the evidence accumulator used a 14-day
half-life and 30-day TTL. An 8-month-old SemiAnalysis HBM article
had decayed to ~0.5^17 ≈ near-zero confidence, so the persistent
signal was effectively dead by the time we could surface it.

Structural bottlenecks (HBM, CoWoS, transformers, HALEU, naval
propulsion) are MULTI-YEAR shifts, not 2-week events. They need
proper persistence in the evidence ledger.

DYNAMIC FIX (no hardcoding)
1. Per-domain decay rates in evidence-accumulator.ts:
     STRUCTURAL nodes (semis / energy / nuclear / defence /
       resources / mfg) → 90-day half-life, 180-day TTL
     CYCLICAL nodes (logistics / agri / capital) → 14-day, 30-day
     This means a SemiAnalysis HBM article from 90 days ago still
     carries 50% of its original weight, instead of <0.001%.

2. New readPersistentBottlenecks() function. Returns the top-K active
   SystemNodes from the ledger, ranked by decay-adjusted confidence
   with a +5 boost for structural nodes (they should surface even
   when cyclical signals momentarily score higher). Includes:
     - confidence_pct, cumulative_score, sample_count
     - last_seen, age_days
     - trend: rising / steady / falling / cooling (computed from
       activity vs domain half-life)
     - is_structural flag
     - top contributing samples

3. Endpoint /api/v1/news?persistent=1 returns the ranked list.

4. New "🚧 PERSISTENT BOTTLENECK READING" panel on the news page,
   above Transformational Contracts. Shows up to 8 active structural
   bottlenecks with confidence%, sample count, age, trend arrow,
   STRUCTURAL badge, and the latest contributing article.

Result: HBM, CoWoS, grid, defence — any structural node with
accumulated evidence — surfaces persistently as a bottleneck reading
even when no fresh news arrived today. Auto-detected. Not hardcoded.
The system identifies them because the evidence is structurally
weighted, not because a developer added them to a list.
